data.text: Not really a fast food kind of girl but dang!! Everyone should at least try Febo at least once. Walking along the streets of Amsterdam, I have seen at least one Febo at every corner I turn. This Dutch fast food chain is seemingly popular and it works like a vending machine where you insert in coins and get the stuff u want. This is so good! It's a spicy croquette stuffed with beef and peanuts.

data.text: И кто нам только сказал, что в Голландии нужно попробовать не только сыр, но и селёдку!!? В каждом ресторане мы искали эту рыбу моей мечты, и все безуспешно. Как назло, только форель, лосось и иже с ними. Все официанты пожимали плечами при нашем "ну,Селдь" (я,конечно,помнила, что на букву "Х" , но слово вылетело из головы!) Herring ,чтоб ее. Это как в России все иностранцы ждут медведей с балалайкой на улице. Короче, в супермаркете купили этот голландский деликатес. Пальчики оближешь,ммм💋

data.text: De Pijp, an Amsterdam neighborhood found just south of the canal ring, translates into English as 'The Pipe’ - an early reference to either the public prostitution or the shape of the neighborhood. Historians disagree.  For the last couple of years, an actual pipe, the Amsterdam metro, has been digging its way under De Pijp. Not surprisingly, building a subway in a city that's below sea level is kind of tricky and led to the misfortune which was the 'Great Heineken Debacle of 2014,' when the Heineken brewery fell into a giant sinkhole. Even without its top tourist destination and the constant fear of sudden, gaping pits, De Pijp has managed to evolve into a neighborhood that lifestyle bloggers describe as “trendy” and “alive.” On sunny afternoons, try Sarphatipark if you're inclined to pop the top and get some color. The Albert Cuyp Market (#albertcuypmarkt) is (supposedly) the “largest daytime market in Europe” and has a few interesting food stands, but you're better off heading to Pho 91 (@pho91amsterdam), Spaghetteria (@spaghetteria_pastabar), or The Butcher (@thebutcheramsterdam). (**TIP - There’s also great Surinamese just off the market on Eerste van der Helststraat.) For shopping, there’s Charlie + Mary (@charlieplusmary), All The Luck In The World… (@alltheluckintheworld), and several other boutiques on the same block of Gerard Doustraat. If you're working away from the office, Stadskantine has plenty of window seating and a good atmosphere. For coffee, Scandinavian Embassy (@scandinavianembassy) and CT Coffee & Coconuts (@coffeecoconuts) are good spots. data.text: I went hunting in my boss' fridge during a late night shift yesterday. Found spinach, pumpkin, lentils, organic cherry tomatoes, salmon and eggs. And I created this finger licking good bowl of veggie awesomeness. Roasted the tomatoes - lentils and pumpkin in the oven with tamari, cumin, ras el hanout and cayenne. Scrambled the eggs with salmon and miso and layered it on top of some fresh spinach. And sprinkled some roasted pumpkinseeds on top. Kind of Moroccan -Japanese fusion thingy. Pretty good. It made me feel at home in an empty loft at 22pm. 🍅🍳🍆 At the moment I'm enjoying a little pre-Easter twosomeparty in rural Tuitjehorn with my Sol-mate 🌞 cooking spicy curries, drinking Syrah #vinnaturel and learning about the healing powers of herbs and other green leafy creatures. Hmm feels good to be out of Amsterdam. I literally have more space in my body and mind.

data.text: #tbt to the best poffertjes in Amsterdam. These little Dutch babies are fluffy, sweet and perfect to pop in your mouth. The best I've had are in Nieuwmarkt Square from a food stand. A must eat every time I'm in Amsterdam.

data.text: The Westerpark hosts several great places to go to for lunch, drinks or an easy dinner. Pacific Parc has gotten some severe nearby competition over the last years (e.g. Mossel & Gin, Brouwerij Troost, Wester Wijnfabriek). These places are run by young, enthusiastic, hospitality minded people. In our multiple visits, we unfortunately didn't get this vibe at Pacific Parc. But hey: the biggest pro is the terrace and the food is ok! The large salads we had were sufficient in size, tasty and fresh. Only the Pata Negra mentioned on the menu was replaced by the cheaper Jamón Serrano.  Do we still come here? Uhm yes. Because the sunny terrace is great and it is a great place if you don't want to cook yourself one night. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Pacific Parc Polonceaukade 23 020-4887778, reservations possible www.pacificparc.nl Open: Mon-Sun 11.00-end ——————————————————————— #dinner #pacificparc #westerpark #mosselengin #westerwijnfabriek #brouwerijtroost #polonceaukade #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #patanegra #jamonserrano #caesarsalad ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites. data.text: We have a Fish and Chips revival in Amsterdam. Viscafé De Gouden Hoek, close to the Westerpark, was the first offering mainly Fish and Chips from daily catches. We love the ambiance which is very stylish and strengthening the concept. Here is what they do menu wise: some classic startes like croquettes, oysters and crab, but the main focus is of course on fish and chips. You choose one of the daily catches and combine it with one of three crusts with accompanying sauce. Choose from the classic crust with remoulade, a panko-crust with piccalilli or tempura-crust with Japanese Sriracha. When you don’t have enough at hand, daily catches ask for good communication between kitchen and service staff. Which in our case didn't go very well. We were surprised when two out of three dishes served had a totally different fish then the one we had ordered. And we had to find out ourselves. Ah what the heck, the taste was good. Service wasn’t to stable though. Some get it, others don’t. Do we recommend this place? Yup! We like the concept, we love the taste, maybe they can improve service a little. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Viscafé De Gouden Hoek Van Limburg Stirumstraat 10A  020-2299009, reservations advised www.degoudenhoek.nl  Open: Tue-Fri 17.00-0.00, Sat-Sun 16.00-0.00 ——— #dinner #fishandchips #westerpark #staatsliedenbuurt #amsterdamwest #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.
